As a Confluence user who uses the "task report" macro to review completed action items I would like to have the ability to filter my task report to only include action items that have been resolved within a certain number hours, days, and weeks from the current date.

This is possible in JIRA with the following JQL statement: "resolved >= -2w"

In confluence you can only filter by "Created after" while at the same time "Dates must be entered as dd-mm-yyyy." This would require a team member to go in and update the dd-mm-yyyy for each meeting.

